        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"382902\">@Yoh Tanimoto</span> can you do this slightly more generally? That is, it seems like we're missing an instance of <code>IsOrderBornology</code> for subtypes, and the lemma for <code>ℝ≥0</code> can be generalized to take an order preserving isometry (which you can then apply to <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=NNReal.toReal#doc\">docs#NNReal.toReal</a>), and probably you can make it even more general than that (maybe an order-preserving <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=LocallyBoundedMap%3F#doc\">docs#LocallyBoundedMap?</a>)</p>",
